solution: ```class Solution {
    public char repeatedCharacter(String s) {
        int mask = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            int bit = 1 << (c - 'a');
            if ((mask & bit) != 0) return c;
            mask |= bit;
        }
        return ' ';
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a single 32-bit integer as a bitmask to track seen characters; each bit represents one lowercase letter. On the first duplicate encounter, the corresponding bit is already set, so the character is returned immediately.

